'''subpage''' - Template for creating navigation links to sub-pages on games.darkrepos.com

==Description==

Creates formatted links to sub-pages using the new folder-based URL structure. Supports both simple links and styled navigation elements.

==Usage==

===Basic Link===
<pre>
{{subpage|Dragon_Quest_III_(SNES)|ROM_Map}}
</pre>
Creates: [[Dragon_Quest_III_(SNES)/ROM_Map|ROM Map]]

===With Custom Display Text===
<pre>
{{subpage|Dragon_Quest_III_(SNES)|ROM_Map|ROM Memory Map}}
</pre>
Creates: [[Dragon_Quest_III_(SNES)/ROM_Map|ROM Memory Map]]

===Nested Sub-page===
<pre>
{{subpage|Dragon_Quest_III_(SNES)|Values/Spells}}
</pre>
Creates: [[Dragon_Quest_III_(SNES)/Values/Spells|Spells]]

==Parameters==

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Required !! Description
|-
| 1 || Yes || Game folder name (e.g., "Dragon_Quest_III_(SNES)")
|-
| 2 || Yes || Sub-page path (e.g., "ROM_Map" or "Values/Spells")
|-
| 3 || No || Custom display text (defaults to last part of path with underscores replaced by spaces)
|}

==URL Structure==

This wiki uses a folder-based URL structure:

<pre>
Game_Name_(Platform)/
├── index.wikitext        (main page)
├── ROM_Map.wikitext
├── RAM_Map.wikitext
├── TBL.wikitext
├── Values/
│   ├── index.wikitext    (values main page)
│   ├── Spells.wikitext
│   └── Items.wikitext
└── ROM_Map/
    ├── Monsters.wikitext
    └── Items.wikitext
</pre>

